      "writtenOn": "2017-12-07T17:34:59Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I originally went with the ifs over the switch because the use of breaks in the loop seemed less readable and I\u0027m pretty sure at some point I got a warning for using default when all the cases were handled. I wanted to have a default since we\u0027re reading this request from a socket so it seemed more likely to accidentally read something wrong and end up with an invalid request type.\n\nUsing continues in the switch instead of breaks seems to solve both those problems.",
      "parentUuid": "deea3a1e_10e0dda5",
      "revId": "93c4d4aa3c7011a29d4d87d11ab3ab780de656e1",
