      "writtenOn": "2017-12-07T17:34:59Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The kIs64Bit request returns this value, which is used to initialize Ptracer. Other options are to pass the target pid (expected to be getppid()) to initialize with, or defer initializing Ptracer until we get the first kAttach request (and return an error if we get any other request first).\n\nI went with is_64_bit here since it\u0027s less work to initialize and for its expected use, we know the target process has the same bitness as the broker.",
